&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to open a &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;URL&lt;/a&gt; in a new tab, as opposed to a popup window.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen related questions where the responses would look something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable language_&quot;&gt;window&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(url,&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;_blank&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable language_&quot;&gt;window&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(url);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But none of them worked for me, the browser still tried to open a popup window.&lt;/p&gt;
